SENATE RESOLUTION—Providing that no allowances will be
paid for the 36th Special Session of the Nevada Legislature
for periodicals, stamps, stationery or communications.
RESOLVED BY THE SENATE OF THE STATE OF NEVADA, That for
the 36th Special Session of the Nevada Legislature, no allowances
will be paid for members of the Senate for periodicals, stamps,
stationery or the use of telephones and no allowances will be paid
for the President Pro Tempore, Majority Leader, Minority Leader or
chair of a committee of the Senate for postage, telephone tolls or
other charges for communications; and be it further
RESOLVED, That this resolution becomes effective upon
adoption.
